Citation.sTitle: Liquid liquid equilibria for the binary system of di-isopropyl ether (DIPE) +water in between 288.15 and 323.15K and the ternary systems of DIPE +water + C1 C4 alcohols at 298.15K
Citation.sAbstract: Binary liquid liquid equilibrium (LLE) data for the system di-isopropyl ether (DIPE) + water were measured at atmospheric pressure from 288.15 to 323.15 K and the ternary LLE for systems of DIPE + water + C1 C4 alcohols (methanol, ethanol, 1-propanol, 2-propanol, 1-butanol and 2-butanol) were also determined at 298.15 K at atmospheric pressure. The experimental binary and ternary LLE data were correlated with the NRTL and UNIQUAC models, respectively.
